05/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police seized about 6kg of heroin, a small amount of marijuana, weapons and explosives in raids on 29 locations across BiH, according to an announcement Tuesday (August 4th) by Banja Luka police spokesperson Mirna Soja. In all, police arrested 14 people during the operation, conducted jointly with Croatian police, who arrested a Bosnian citizen in Croatia. Police are searching for five other suspects. Investigators from both countries have been working on the case since April. (Fena, RTRS, Pincom.info, AP - 04/08/09)
